cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for solving the Closest Vector Problem (CVP) and improving on existing techniques. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves the use of randomness in the algorithm. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with the Voronoi graph and its properties. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves optimization and finding the closest vector, which can be relevant in some machine learning applications. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the complexity of the CVP and improving on existing algorithms.
